Nimo's vimrc
https://github.com/nimo1491/vimrc


--------------
How to Install
--------------

1. Check out from github

    a. Windows

        * Execute git-bash. Please click "Run as administrator" in the vista/win7.

        * Go to the location of Vim directory.

            $ cd /c/Program\ Files/Vim

        * Clone vimrc.

            $ git clone https://github.com/nimo1491/vimrc ./.vim

        * Download exuberant ctags fomr http://ctags.sourceforge.net and put ctags.exe in the Vim directory.
        
    b. Linux

        $ git clone https://github.com/nimo1491/vimrc ~/.vim

2. Update submodules

    $ cd .vim
    $ git submodule update --init

3. Install vimrc 

    $ ./install.sh


----------------------
Upgrade Plugin Bundles
----------------------

All plugins were checked out as git submodules, which can be upgraded with `git pull`.
For example, to upgrade nerdtree: 

    $ cd .vim/bundle/nerdtree
    $ git pull


------------
Key Mappings
------------

1. Build-in 

    <s-h>     Switch to previous tab.
    <s-l>     Switch to next tab.
    <         Shift left in visual mode.
    >         Shift right in visual mode.
    <c-j>     Move down and maximum the split.
    <c-k>     Move up and maximum the split.
    <c-l>     Move right and maximum the split.
    <c-h>     Move left and maximum the split.
    <c-a>     Command line <home>
    <c-e>     Command line <end>
    <c-b>     Command line <left>
    <c-d>     Command line <del>
    <c-f>     Command line <right>
    <c-n>     Command line <down>
    <c-p>     Command line <up>
    :cd.      Change working directory to that of current file.
    :w!!      Force writing if you forgot to sudo.
    ,/        Turn off searching highlighting.
    ,p        Toggles paste mode.
    ,r        Replace the current word in all opened buffers.
    ,g        Generates the header guard.
    ,q        Toggles quickfix.
    ,]        Go to next quickfix error.
    ,[        Go to previous quickfix error.

2. Plugins

    ,e        Toggles nerd tree.
    ,t        Toggles taglist.
    ,k        Autoclose(move up).
    ,j        Autoclose(move down).
    ,h        Autoclose(move left).
    ,l        Autoclose(move right).
    ,<space>  Supertab default key.
    ,<tab>    Switch supertab between <tab> and <leader><space>.
    ,ff       Fuzzy finder files.
    ,fb       Fuzzy finder buffers.


-------
Plugins
-------

* [Pathogen] Pathogen let us install a plugin as a bundle in ~/.vim/bundle seprately.

* [Nerd Tree] A tree explorer plugin for navigating the filesystem.

* [Nerd Commenter] Allows for easy commenting of code for many filetypes.

* [Taglist] A source code browsers.

* [FuzzyFinder] Buffer/file/command/tag/etc explorer with fuzzy matching.

* [AutoClose] Inserts matching bracket, paren, brace or quote.

* [Vim-surround] Deal with pairs of surroundings.

* [Matchit] Extended % matching for HTML, LaTeX, and many other languages. 

* [Xmledit] XML/HTML tags will be completed automatically.

* [SuperTab] Do all your insert-mode completion with Tab.

* [SnipMate] TextMate-style snippets for Vim

* [YankRing] Maintains a history of previous yanks, changes and deletes 
  
* [VisIncr] Produce increasing/decreasing columns of numbers, dates, or daynames.
  
* [Cute Error Marker] Showing error and warning icons on line.

* [OmniCppComplete] C/C++ omni-completion with ctags database.

* [JavaComplete] Java Omni-completion.


--------------------------
Language Supports
--------------------------

* HTML, Javascript, Python, CSS, C, C++, Java: use `TAB` to do omni-completion.
* HTML/XML: End tags are automatically completed after typing a begin tag. (Typing > twice pushes the end tag to a new line.)


